Package algorithms.trees

Class TDP_Unranked_Iterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.trees.TDP_Iterator
      • algorithms.trees.TDP_Unranked_Iterator
  • public class TDP_Unranked_Iterator
extends TDP_Iterator
    An UNranked enumeration algorithm for a T-DP problem specified by a entities.paths.TDP_Problem_Instance object. It is implemented as an iterator that is first initialized and then the method get_next() returns the next T-DP solution in an arbitrary order. Unranked enumeration is implemented as a Lawler procedure without any PQs, thus yielding constant delay (if the number of stages is constant).
    Author:
    Nikolaos Tziavelis

    • Field Detail

      • global_q

        protected Queue<TDP_Prefix_Solution> global_q
        Maintains all the prefix solutions that are not yet expanded.

      • latest_solution

        protected TDP_Prefix_Solution latest_solution
        Stores the solution returned in the previous call of get_next(). This is required because candidates generated from the k'th solution are found and inserted into the list in the (k+1)'th call.

      • latest_sidetrack_stage

        protected int latest_sidetrack_stage
        The stage in which latest_solution made a sidetrack (by going to a successor). It is the same as the length of the prefix that we popped in the previous call of get_next(), that was then expanded to latest_solution. By convention, latest_sidetrack_stage of the first solution is 1.
